<li id="cite_note-25"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25" title="">^</a></b> For more on Section 2 go to <a href="http://caselaw.lp.findlaw.com/data/constitution/amendment14/36.html#1" class="external text" title="http://caselaw.lp.findlaw.com/data/constitution/amendment14/36.html#1" rel="nofollow">Findlaw.com</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-26"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFChin2004">Chin, Gabriel J. (2004). "Reconstruction, Felon Disenfranchisement, and the Right to Vote: Did the Fifteenth Amendment Repeal Section 2 of the Fourteenth?". <i>Georgetown Law Journal</i> <b>92</b>: 259. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:10.139/ssrn.10.139/ssrn.433580 (inactive 2009-04-04).</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Reconstruction%2C+Felon+Disenfranchisement%2C+and+the+Right+to+Vote%3A+Did+the+Fifteenth+Amendment+Repeal+Section+2+of+the+Fourteenth%3F&amp;rft.jtitle=Georgetown+Law+Journal&amp;rft.aulast=Chin&amp;rft.aufirst=Gabriel+J.&amp;rft.au=Chin%2C+Gabriel+J.&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.volume=92&amp;rft.pages=259&amp;rft_id=info:doi/10.139%2Fssrn.10.139%2Fssrn.433580&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Fourteenth_Amendment_to_the_United_States_Constitution"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
